## Check User ZPK

Check if the zpk is expired. The zpk is used to authenticate a user.

> Definition

```text
POST <%= config[:api_host] %>user/checkzpk
```

> Example Request

```shell
$ curl <%= config[:api_host] %>user/checkzpk \
    -d api_key=<%= config[:ex_api_key] %> \
    -d api_secret=<%= config[:ex_api_secret] %> \
    -d zpk=<USER_ZPK> 
```

```javascript
var Zoom = require("zoomus")({
    key : "<YOUR_API_KEY>",
    secret : "<YOUR_API_SECRET>"
});

Zoom.user.checkZPK({
    zpk : "<USER_ZPK>"
});
```

> Example Response

```json
{
  "expire_in": 7187
}
```

Arguments | &nbsp;
--- | ---
zpk **required** | User zpk.